<exercise checkit-seed="0001" checkit-slug="F1" checkit-title="Simple Interest">
    <statement>
       
                <p>
                    Tao recently had some financial trouble, and as a result they had to borrow $2,900 in the form of a simple interest loan with an annual interest rate of 8%. They plan to pay the loan off in one large payment after 10 months.
                    <ol>
                        <li> How much interest does the loan generate over the 10 months? </li>
                        <li> How much will Tao have to pay off at the end of the loan?</li>
                    </ol>
                </p>         
        
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <p>
            <ol>
                <li> The loan generates <m>I = P_0 r t = 2900(0.08\cdot \frac{10}{12}) =</m>$193.33 in interest.</li>
                <li> They will need to pay 2,900 + 193.33 = $3,093.33 at the end of the loan.</li>
            </ol>
        </p>
    </answer>
</exercise>
